Dynamics
Market Growth
The market is expected to grow from USD 7.28 billion in 2024 to USD 10.82 billion by 2029, at a CAGR of 8.22%.
Material Types
Silicone elastomers are projected to be the most dominant type of conductive silicones between 2016 and 2021.
Applications
The thermal interface materials segment is the fastest-growing application in the global conductive silicone market.
Regional Growth
Asia-Pacific is projected to register high growth, in terms of value, between 2016 and 2021.
Key Drivers and Challenges
Drivers
Increasing demand for electronic components in power generation & distribution and the LED industry.
Growing per capita silicone demand in Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa regions.
Continuous expansion and new product development activities undertaken by different companies.
Challenges
High raw material prices, such as silicon metal and methyl chloride, affecting market growth.
